5
00:01:56,575 --> 00:01:58,498
Crazy-drivin' motherfucker.

6
00:01:59,286 --> 00:02:00,913
- Shit.
- Come on.

7
00:02:03,373 --> 00:02:06,172
Hey! Hey, Marvin,
what are you doin'?

8
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:08,629
- He's mine, Jack. Get lost.
- Fuck you he's yours, he's mine.

9
00:02:08,837 --> 00:02:10,589
Eddie assigned this guy to me.
What the hell are you doing'?

10
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:11,844
Well then go
straighten it out with Eddie.

11
00:02:12,007 --> 00:02:13,054
I'll collect the money.

12
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:15,135
I almost got killed
tryin' to get this guy.

13
00:02:15,344 --> 00:02:17,142
- He shot at me--
- Back off, goddamn it!

14
00:02:17,346 --> 00:02:18,848
I said I'm takin' him, all right?

15
00:02:19,056 --> 00:02:20,933
- All right, Marvin.
- This guy's worth $1,200!

16
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:21,892
Okay, okay Marvin.

17
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,818
What the hell are we fightin' for?
We're friends- -

18
00:02:24,019 --> 00:02:26,442
Nothin' personal, Jack,
but fuck off, all right?

19
00:02:26,647 --> 00:02:28,866
Take it easy. Jesus!

20
00:02:29,441 --> 00:02:30,863
Marvin, watch out!

21
00:02:32,069 --> 00:02:34,413
What the fuck's goin' on?
You guys ain't cops.

22
00:02:34,655 --> 00:02:36,498
No, we're ballet dancers.

23
00:02:36,907 --> 00:02:39,660
Didn't your mother ever teach you
how to react to strangers?

24
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:41,495
Not shoot at them? Huh?

25
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:58,762
Hey, Marvin, thanks for the car.

26
00:02:59,638 --> 00:03:02,141
You sleep,
and I'll bring it back a little later.

27
00:03:03,225 --> 00:03:04,943
[engine starts]

28
00:03:24,371 --> 00:03:26,339
Got a delivery for you, Gooch.

29
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:29,467
Jack. The soda machine's been out
for a week and a half.

30
00:03:31,837 --> 00:03:33,305
Check that for me, would ya?

31
00:03:33,797 --> 00:03:35,424
What do we got here?

32
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,017
Alright.

33
00:03:38,885 --> 00:03:41,729
- Give you any trouble?
- Did you give me any trouble?

34
00:03:41,972 --> 00:03:44,020
- Fuck you, man!
- He didn't give me any trouble.

35
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:45,646
Fuck you, too, man!

36
00:03:45,851 --> 00:03:48,104
- Move!
- I know my motherfuckin' rights!

37
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:53,484
Slap it.

38
00:04:41,531 --> 00:04:43,659
Moscone's Bail Bonds.

39
00:04:46,036 --> 00:04:49,631
No, it's cash only.
No checks, no cards.

40
00:04:50,165 --> 00:04:54,762
I'm sorry, ma'am. That's the policy.
I wish I could help you out. Sorry.

41
00:04:58,215 --> 00:05:00,058
Just dropped off Bouchet. Is Eddie in?

42
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:02,477
So you finally caught someone, Jack.

43
00:05:02,719 --> 00:05:04,437
Jerry, is he in?

44
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:06,640
I think that's terrific.

45
00:05:07,349 --> 00:05:09,317
Jack, I been tryin' to reach
you since last night.

46
00:05:09,518 --> 00:05:10,519
What do you got for me?

47
00:05:10,727 --> 00:05:12,479
Been tryin' to reach me? It's Bouchet.

48
00:05:12,729 --> 00:05:14,606
Ooh, Bouchet. Good score, Jack.
$900, right?

49
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:15,987
No, it's $1,200.

50
00:05:16,274 --> 00:05:19,244
- No, $900.
- That's, that's $1,200. Come on.

51
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:21,242
No. Yeah, you're right.

52
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:24,536
My stomach's killin' me.

53
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:25,913
<i>I'm gain' over
to Chin Leo's for breakfast.</i>

54
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:28,870
- I want to talk to you.
- About what?

55
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:32,499
- I'll talk to you over there.
- Could I have my money first?

56
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:34,717
Of course.

57
00:05:35,043 --> 00:05:36,636
What, do you think
I'm gonna try and stiff you?

58
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:38,931
You? Never!
He would never try and stiff me.

59
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:40,552
Do I detect some kind of sarcasm here?

60
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:41,679
Never.

61
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:43,851
Where have
I inherited this reputation?

62
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:45,850
I have never done business
with anybody,

63
00:05:46,054 --> 00:05:47,271
and Jerry is my witness...

64
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:49,395
...that I have ever, ever, ever...

65
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:50,441
Has that phone ever rang...

66
00:05:50,642 --> 00:05:53,236
Has that phone ever rang
with a complaint about me?

67
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:56,068
Never, never. So let's go.
I'll buy you some breakfast.

68
00:05:56,273 --> 00:05:57,115
I don't eat breakfast.

69
00:05:57,274 --> 00:05:58,901
Well then, have an early lunch.
Let's go.

70
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:04,781
You ever hear of a guy
named Jonathan Mardukas?

71
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:07,243
- The Duke. Yeah, I know who he is.
- What do you know?

72
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:09,327
He's that accountant that
embezzled a couple of million

73
00:06:09,536 --> 00:06:11,379
from some Vegas wise guy
and he gave it to charity.

74
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:12,422
That's very good.

75
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:15,876
Only thing is, that it wasn't a couple
of million. It was $15 million.

76
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:19,012
It wasn't some Vegas wise guy.
It was Jimmy Serrano.

77
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:22,265
I know, I know.
I can read the papers.

78
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:25,219
Look, I don't want to
bring up the past, but...

79
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:27,520
...isn't Serrano the guy
that ran you

80
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:29,894
out of Chicago when he
was runnin' things back there?

81
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:31,065
He didn't run me out.

82
00:06:31,266 --> 00:06:34,019
Yeah, right right right. You gave
up bein' a cop to do this shit?

83
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:37,856
- Alright, what's the point?
- The point, Jack:

84
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:41,485
I bailed out the accountant.
I didn't know who he was at the time.

85
00:06:41,693 --> 00:06:44,572
I mean, had I known there was
no way I would've put up the bond.

86
00:06:44,779 --> 00:06:46,122
I mean it's only a matter of time

87
00:06:46,323 --> 00:06:48,576
before Serrano vanishes
this guy from the planet

88
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:50,540
and I'm out $450,000.

89
00:06:50,744 --> 00:06:52,792
You're out $450,000 on this guy?

90
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:54,130
- No.
- No.

91
00:06:54,331 --> 00:06:56,425
No, because I got you,
and you're the best,

92
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:58,798
and you're gonna find him
and bring him back.

93
00:06:59,002 --> 00:07:00,299
Yeah, right.

94
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:02,426
How do you even know
this guy is still alive?

95
00:07:02,631 --> 00:07:06,636
Because this guy is crazy.
He sends postcards to Serrano.

96
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:09,437
He's tellin' him what a great time
he's havin' with his money.

97
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:11,890
How much time you got left?

98
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:14,435
Friday, midnight, I default.
I eat the $450,000.

99
00:07:14,643 --> 00:07:16,645
This Friday? That's five days.

100
00:07:16,853 --> 00:07:19,026
Forget it. You go find him,
give me my money.

101
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:20,322
Jack, alright, look.
Listen to me.

102
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:23,117
I'll give you $40...
I'll give you $50,000.

103
00:07:23,318 --> 00:07:26,117
$50,000? I gotta chase you down
for $1,200. Forget about it.

104
00:07:26,321 --> 00:07:29,200
- No, no, no, no, Jack, please.
- Jack, nothing, forget about it. What else you got?

105
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:30,784
I ain't got nothin', this is it.

106
00:07:30,992 --> 00:07:33,245
If you don't find this guy,
I'm out of business.

107
00:07:34,204 --> 00:07:35,501
Eddie...

108
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:38,212
I'll do it for $100,000.

109
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:40,760
$100,000? Are you out of your mind?
This is an easy gig.

110
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:42,554
It's a midnight run for Chrissakes.

111
00:07:42,754 --> 00:07:45,223
Maybe you haven't noticed,
but I'm tired of gettin' shot at.

112
00:07:45,423 --> 00:07:47,425
I'm tired of this
miserable fuckin' business,

113
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:48,977
every lowlife that I run into.

114
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:51,225
If you're gonna pay me,
you gotta pay me what's right.

115
00:07:51,429 --> 00:07:53,852
You want me for this job,
give me what's right.

116
00:07:54,057 --> 00:07:55,980
First of all,
the guy is an accountant.

117
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:57,401
He's not gonna shoot you.

118
00:07:57,602 --> 00:08:00,321
All you have to do is find him.
You put him in a bag,

119
00:08:00,522 --> 00:08:02,024
hit him with a rubber hose,
bring him home.

120
00:08:02,232 --> 00:08:03,779
That's easy for you to say,
listen to me,

121
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:07,033
it's $100,000, no more, no less,
and I want a contract.

122
00:08:07,237 --> 00:08:09,831
- Contract?
- That's right, I want it in writing.

123
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:12,625
$100,000, and I'll have the Duke
here for you by Friday night.

124
00:08:12,826 --> 00:08:14,874
Now, can I have my $1,200, please?

125
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:21,923
Man, you do worse than any crook
I ever put a bond up for.

126
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:32,470
Stanley?

127
00:08:33,221 --> 00:08:34,438
Stan.

128
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:40,191
Hey, Big Dog. How are you?

129
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:42,405
What are you doin' here?

130
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:44,107
Listen, I need a favor.

131
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:47,068
I need to see the booking slip
of a Jonathan Mardukas.

132
00:08:47,277 --> 00:08:49,075
M-A-R-D-U-K-A-S.

133
00:08:49,279 --> 00:08:51,077
There you go.

134
00:08:57,454 --> 00:08:59,923
- Yes, sir.
- What's that?

135
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:03,969
The number he called
right after he was arrested.

136
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:07,930
212 area code.

137
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:10,467
Looks like I'm goin' to New York.

138
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:19,268
Are you Jack Walsh?

139
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:22,649
- Excuse me.
- Are you Jack Walsh?

140
00:09:22,854 --> 00:09:25,858
- I'm sorry, do I know you?
- Alonzo Mosely, FBI.

141
00:09:26,316 --> 00:09:29,069
That's a nice badge.
How can I get one of those?

142
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:30,494
I want to talk to you, Jack.

143
00:09:30,695 --> 00:09:32,413
Yeah? Why don't you
call my social secretary?

144
00:09:32,614 --> 00:09:35,037
Yeah, very funny.
I want to talk to you.

145
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:37,452
Take your hands off me!

146
00:09:40,121 --> 00:09:41,247
Jeez.

147
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:42,916
Take it easy!

148
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,587
You know it's a $10 fine
for jaywalking in Los Angeles?

149
00:09:47,796 --> 00:09:48,922
Shut up.

150
00:09:49,172 --> 00:09:50,298
What I want to know is

151
00:09:50,507 --> 00:09:53,761
are you working on anything
having to do with Jonathan Mardukas?

152
00:09:54,677 --> 00:09:56,350
Never heard of him.

153
00:09:56,554 --> 00:09:58,477
Well, I believe you have heard of him.

154
00:09:59,891 --> 00:10:01,438
Let me tell you something, asshole.

155
00:10:01,643 --> 00:10:03,395
We've been working on
this Jimmy Serrano thing

156
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:05,321
for about six years.

157
00:10:05,563 --> 00:10:07,531
Mardukas is my shot.

158
00:10:07,774 --> 00:10:09,947
I'm gonna bring him into federal court

159
00:10:10,151 --> 00:10:12,028
and I don't want any
third rate rent-a-thug

160
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:13,955
who couldn't cut it
as a cop in Chicago

161
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:17,079
bringing him to LA
on some bullshit local charge.

162
00:10:26,126 --> 00:10:27,969
Do I make myself understood?

163
00:10:28,503 --> 00:10:30,130
Can I ask you something?

164
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:33,429
These sunglasses, they're really nice.

165
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:34,885
Are they government issued

166
00:10:35,093 --> 00:10:37,767
or do all you guys go to, like,
the same store to get them?

167
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:43,609
Do I make myself understood?

168
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:45,437
Can't you take a joke?

169
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:48,402
Get him out of here.

170
00:10:50,108 --> 00:10:51,234
No, let's talk some more.

171
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:52,534
Get the fuck out of here.

172
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:54,408
If I hear anything,
I'll let you know.

173
00:10:54,612 --> 00:10:56,330
Good-bye. Have a nice day.

174
00:11:00,326 --> 00:11:02,124
Think I could have my sunglasses back?

175
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:03,295
Here's your sunglasses.

176
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:05,248
[engine revs]

177
00:11:07,959 --> 00:11:11,179
Thanks. Thanks for this, too.

178
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:16,976
"Alonzo Mosely."

179
00:11:17,969 --> 00:11:19,346
Alonzo.

180
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:08,019
How's that?

181
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:10,738
Looks fine to me.

182
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:13,692
Harold Longman, please.

183
00:12:15,652 --> 00:12:18,451
Harry? Jack Walsh.
How're you doin'?

184
00:12:18,655 --> 00:12:21,750
You got that address check
on that phone number for me?

185
00:12:24,244 --> 00:12:25,416
Uh-huh.

186
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:29,541
Okay, thanks a lot, Harry.
Say hello to Julie for me. Okay, bye.

187
00:12:31,209 --> 00:12:32,961
Thank you.

188
00:12:35,797 --> 00:12:37,674
You Jack Walsh?

189
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:41,845
- Who wants to know?
- That's a "Yes."

190
00:12:42,262 --> 00:12:44,014
We'd really like to have
a word with you.

191
00:12:44,222 --> 00:12:47,442
- Yeah? What about?
- It involves big cash, lot of prizes.

192
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:49,318
I'll make it short and sweet.

193
00:12:49,519 --> 00:12:52,113
The people I work for are really
interested in your visit here.

194
00:12:52,313 --> 00:12:53,781
Oh yeah? Who are the
people you work for?

195
00:12:53,982 --> 00:12:56,360
An old friend of yours
from the Chicago days.

196
00:12:57,777 --> 00:12:58,949
You're here for the Duke.

197
00:12:59,153 --> 00:13:01,201
You think he's in New York,
and we think you're right.

198
00:13:01,406 --> 00:13:03,784
That's a nice jacket.
What is it, goatskin?

199
00:13:03,992 --> 00:13:06,791
Come on, Joey, please. Will you?
Never mind him.

200
00:13:07,495 --> 00:13:08,917
The way I hear it,

201
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,791
you didn't cooperate
with my boss a few years back.

202
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:13,210
Is that the way you heard it?

203
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:15,420
Yeah, but I got a
news flash for you, Jack.

204
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:16,971
He'd pay a hell of a lot more
for the Duke

205
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:18,473
than that putz bail bondsman
back in LA.

206
00:13:18,673 --> 00:13:21,472
- Oh yeah? How much more?
- How about a one with six zeros?

207
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:25,813
Are you gonna propose?

208
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:27,147
- Propose?
- Propose.

209
00:13:27,348 --> 00:13:28,725
'Cause if you're not,
quit starin' at me.

210
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:30,105
- Okay?
- Starin' at you?

211
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:32,483
- You're staring at me.
- Joey, back off, will you please? C'mon.

212
00:13:32,687 --> 00:13:36,783
Mr. Walsh, your car's located
in space number 206.

213
00:13:36,983 --> 00:13:39,532
You can catch our shuttle bus
just through these doors.

214
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:40,198
Thank you.

215
00:13:40,194 --> 00:13:42,913
Here's my number, Jack.
Ask for Tony Darvo. That's me.

216
00:13:43,114 --> 00:13:44,957
They'll put you through
to wherever I am.

217
00:13:45,116 --> 00:13:47,665
And be good to
yourself this time. Okay?

218
00:13:51,331 --> 00:13:53,129
Tell Jimmy I said hello.

219
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,537
[phone ringing]

220
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:30,996
- [Woman]: Hello?
- Hello? Mrs. Nelson?

221
00:14:31,204 --> 00:14:32,171
<i>Yes</i> g

222
00:14:32,372 --> 00:14:33,965
Alonzo Mosely,
Federal Bureau of Investigation.

223
00:14:34,207 --> 00:14:36,881
- How are you this afternoon?
- I'm fine.

224
00:14:37,085 --> 00:14:39,588
Let me get right to the
point if I may, Mrs. Nelson.

225
00:14:39,796 --> 00:14:42,265
An agent in our Los Angeles office
discovered a detail

226
00:14:42,465 --> 00:14:44,217
that was somehow overlooked until now.

227
00:14:44,425 --> 00:14:46,473
It seems that when a
Jonathan Mardukas was arrested

228
00:14:46,677 --> 00:14:50,102
you were the first person he called.
Is that correct, Mrs. Nelson?

229
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:53,852
- <i>Are you there, Mrs. Nelson?
- Yes.</i>

230
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:56,438
Needless to say, this is a
matter of great concern to us,

231
00:14:56,646 --> 00:14:57,989
and if it would not
be too much trouble,

232
00:14:58,189 --> 00:14:59,190
we would like you to come down

233
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:03,029
tomorrow morning to 26 Federal Plaza.
Do you think you could do that?

234
00:15:03,277 --> 00:15:05,325
- I suppose so.
- About 9:00 a.m.?

235
00:15:06,614 --> 00:15:09,493
- Yes.
- Just ask for Agent Alonzo Mosely.

236
00:15:09,742 --> 00:15:12,370
Thanks for your cooperation.
Have a nice day.

237
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,814
[phone dialing]

238
00:15:32,849 --> 00:15:34,101
[phone ringing]

239
00:15:34,308 --> 00:15:36,777
<i>- Hello?
- Dana? it's Helen.</i>

240
00:15:36,978 --> 00:15:38,025
<i>The FBI just called.</i>

241
00:15:38,229 --> 00:15:39,572
<i>They want to speak to me
about Jonathan.</i>

242
00:15:39,772 --> 00:15:43,322
<i>- Oh, my God! Helen.
- [Jonathan]: Helen, what's going on?</i>

243
00:15:43,526 --> 00:15:44,823
<i>[Helen]: Jonathan,
the FBI just called.</i>

