of a bitch my fellow officers

947
00:59:43,246 --> 00:59:46,921
mysteriously discovered seven pounds
of heroin in my house.

948
00:59:47,417 --> 00:59:50,512
So this big-time drug dealer
gave me a choice:

949
00:59:50,754 --> 00:59:52,927
Get on the payroll
like everybody else,

950
00:59:53,131 --> 00:59:55,725
get out of town,
or go to jail for 30 years.

951
00:59:56,760 --> 00:59:58,603
Well, I didn't get on the payroll.

952
00:59:59,179 --> 01:00:00,806
And that's why I do this.

953
01:00:01,765 --> 01:00:04,439
When I find a criminal like you,
I bring him in.

954
01:00:04,643 --> 01:00:07,146
I don't have to worry
about anybody takin' a payoff

955
01:00:07,354 --> 01:00:09,573
because there is no anybody.
There's just me.

956
01:00:19,116 --> 01:00:21,494
Why don't you
get yourself a new watch?

957
01:00:22,077 --> 01:00:23,704
I'll tell you when I know you better.

958
01:00:23,912 --> 01:00:26,586
When you know me better? When will you get
to know me better? I'll get to know you better.

959
01:00:26,790 --> 01:00:29,134
- You're not gonna get to know me better.
- Will you shut up?

960
01:00:29,334 --> 01:00:30,711
That's what I mean.

961
01:00:51,398 --> 01:00:53,492
How much money do we have left?

962
01:00:57,237 --> 01:00:58,989
- That's it?
- That's it.

963
01:01:00,574 --> 01:01:02,702
We're starvin',
and you're buying cigarettes?

964
01:01:02,909 --> 01:01:04,252
I need these cigarettes.

965
01:01:04,452 --> 01:01:07,001
You can have your whatever
you're gonna have, I'll have this.

966
01:01:07,497 --> 01:01:08,965
What can I do for you boys?

967
01:01:09,166 --> 01:01:10,292
Coffee, please.

968
01:01:14,337 --> 01:01:16,760
- How much is the coffee?
- It's 53 cents.

969
01:01:17,007 --> 01:01:19,430
- How much is tea?
- 53 cents.

970
01:01:22,888 --> 01:01:24,310
I'll have tea.

971
01:01:24,556 --> 01:01:27,184
Our breakfast special today
is chorizo and eggs.

972
01:01:27,392 --> 01:01:29,736
- Chorizo and eggs?
- Chorizo and eggs. Yes.

973
01:01:29,978 --> 01:01:32,072
- What is that?
- It's a Mexican sausage

974
01:01:32,272 --> 01:01:35,276
mixed in with scrambled eggs.
It comes with hash browns and toast.

975
01:01:35,483 --> 01:01:37,656
We won't be havin' that. Thank you.

976
01:01:43,700 --> 01:01:45,122
What time you got?

977
01:01:47,495 --> 01:01:48,417
Ten to nine.

978
01:01:48,622 --> 01:01:51,592
Alright, in 10 minutes we'll be
at the Western Union office, we'll have $500,

979
01:01:51,750 --> 01:01:54,924
and I'll buy you a nice juicy steak
or whatever you want, okay?

980
01:01:56,004 --> 01:01:58,883
- Chorizo and eggs?
- Huh?

981
01:01:58,882 --> 01:02:01,431
- Chorizo and eggs?
- I'll get you whatever you want.

982
01:02:05,305 --> 01:02:06,147
You know, Jon,

983
01:02:06,348 --> 01:02:08,851
you're in this mess
because you're in this mess.

984
01:02:09,017 --> 01:02:10,610
I didn't put you in this mess.

985
01:02:10,852 --> 01:02:12,274
Do you understand?

986
01:02:12,479 --> 01:02:13,776
Yeah.

987
01:02:13,980 --> 01:02:17,610
If you had left Jimmy Serrano alone,
this wouldn't be happening.

988
01:02:20,403 --> 01:02:21,950
Thank you.

989
01:02:23,573 --> 01:02:24,449
Thank you.

990
01:02:24,616 --> 01:02:26,664
I had a way out of this, you know.

991
01:02:27,577 --> 01:02:29,124
Oh, yeah
7?

992
01:02:29,287 --> 01:02:32,086
What's the thing
Serrano's most afraid of?

993
01:02:35,001 --> 01:02:37,299
<i>Gain' cross-country with you.</i>

994
01:02:41,633 --> 01:02:43,977
Gettin' knocked off by his own people.

995
01:02:45,178 --> 01:02:47,522
What I know about
his financial transactions

996
01:02:47,722 --> 01:02:50,976
could not only put him away but
every mob guy he ever did business with.

997
01:02:51,226 --> 01:02:53,274
That's why he wants to kill me.

998
01:02:53,687 --> 01:02:56,611
I was gonna put all his records
on computer disks.

999
01:02:56,898 --> 01:02:59,902
I figured if things got too rough
I could always trade them for my life.

1000
01:03:00,110 --> 01:03:01,032
So what happened?

1001
01:03:01,236 --> 01:03:04,706
What happened was I got arrested
before I had a chance to do it.

1002
01:03:05,240 --> 01:03:07,459
Why didn't you just leave him alone?

1003
01:03:08,201 --> 01:03:11,205
You don't look like the kind of guy
who'd be involved in that sort of--

1004
01:03:11,413 --> 01:03:14,007
Why didn't you just leave
that heroin dealer alone?

1005
01:03:16,167 --> 01:03:18,135
I was a mob accountant.

1006
01:03:18,878 --> 01:03:21,301
I thought I worked
in a legitimate firm.

1007
01:03:21,756 --> 01:03:24,179
When I found out I was managing
accounts that were fronts for Serrano

1008
01:03:24,384 --> 01:03:26,261
I couldn't just sit back and do nothing.

1009
01:03:26,469 --> 01:03:28,722
Yeah, but Jon, you still took
what didn't belong to you.

1010
01:03:28,930 --> 01:03:30,773
How can you be
on the side of a mobster?

1011
01:03:30,974 --> 01:03:33,523
- I'm not on the side of a mobster.
- You're on his side if you're not on my side.

1012
01:03:33,727 --> 01:03:35,650
I'm not on anybody's side.
I got nothing to do with it.

1013
01:03:35,854 --> 01:03:37,322
You got everything to do with it.

1014
01:03:37,522 --> 01:03:39,695
You're takin' me to jail
and in jail you know I'll be killed.

1015
01:03:39,899 --> 01:03:42,197
- That's not my problem.
- It's not your problem?

1016
01:03:42,402 --> 01:03:44,029
It's not your problem?

1017
01:03:45,947 --> 01:03:48,075
Did you read about me in the papers?

1018
01:03:48,533 --> 01:03:50,160
- Yeah, I did.
- Were you on my side then?

1019
01:03:50,368 --> 01:03:52,086
- Yeah, I was.
- Then why aren't you now?

1020
01:03:52,287 --> 01:03:54,790
- Because now you're in my way.
- I'm in your way?

1021
01:03:54,998 --> 01:03:57,092
What you mean is you want the money
for turning me in

1022
01:03:57,292 --> 01:04:01,342
because that's all you're about.
You're just about the fuckin' money.

1023
01:04:04,591 --> 01:04:06,343
Hey, Jon.

1024
01:04:06,718 --> 01:04:08,686
You can think
whatever you want to think.

1025
01:04:08,887 --> 01:04:12,812
Doesn't matter to me, 'cause I'm gettin'
my $100,000 any which way you want it.

1026
01:04:21,066 --> 01:04:22,739
Let's go.

1027
01:04:27,197 --> 01:04:29,950
Hey, Tony.
Tony, Hopalong Cassidy.

1028
01:04:30,158 --> 01:04:31,705
You got your camera?
Take a picture.

1029
01:04:31,910 --> 01:04:33,287
Come on,
they got these at the airport.

1030
01:04:33,495 --> 01:04:34,667
Should I get one
on the way back?

1031
01:04:34,871 --> 01:04:35,963
Come on. Put that away.

1032
01:04:36,164 --> 01:04:38,041
I'm not gonna tell you again.

1033
01:04:39,334 --> 01:04:41,632
Tony, there they are.

1034
01:04:51,429 --> 01:04:53,352
- How you doin', Jack?
- Shit.

1035
01:04:53,556 --> 01:04:55,149
Jimmy sends his regards.

1036
01:04:56,851 --> 01:04:58,228
Don't worry, Jack.

1037
01:04:58,436 --> 01:05:01,064
We're not here for you.
We're here for him.

1038
01:05:02,899 --> 01:05:04,116
What are you starin' at?

1039
01:05:04,359 --> 01:05:05,906
Are you gonna propose?

1040
01:05:08,905 --> 01:05:10,031
Drop 'em!

1041
01:05:10,240 --> 01:05:12,459
I said, "Drop 'em," assholes!

1042
01:05:17,747 --> 01:05:19,215
Who the fuck are you guys?

1043
01:05:19,416 --> 01:05:20,918
Who the fuck are you?

1044
01:05:26,673 --> 01:05:30,177
You're dead.
You know who you're fuckin' with?

1045
01:05:30,385 --> 01:05:32,479
No. Why don't you tell me about it?

1046
01:05:32,679 --> 01:05:35,182
Make sure you speak
into the microphone.

1047
01:05:36,891 --> 01:05:38,313
Marvin, Marvin!

1048
01:05:39,894 --> 01:05:42,488
Very clever, Jack. Now give me the keys.

1049
01:05:43,064 --> 01:05:44,782
Come on! Give me the keys!

1050
01:05:45,692 --> 01:05:47,035
Keys.

1051
01:05:50,238 --> 01:05:51,956
Looks like a package deal
to me, Marvin.

1052
01:05:52,490 --> 01:05:54,618
Goddamn it. Come on! Both of you!

1053
01:05:57,954 --> 01:05:59,706
Who the hell were those guys?

1054
01:05:59,914 --> 01:06:02,008
- Marvin, you did it this time.
- What are you talkin' about?

1055
01:06:02,208 --> 01:06:03,801
Those are hired killers back there.

1056
01:06:04,002 --> 01:06:06,425
- Hired to kill who?
- Hired to kill this guy.

1057
01:06:06,629 --> 01:06:09,303
- Me. Me, can you believe it?
- Hired by who?

1058
01:06:09,507 --> 01:06:11,851
Hired by who? Jimmy Serrano.
That's who.

1059
01:06:12,051 --> 01:06:14,145
Oh, fuck.
Why do they want to kill this guy?

1060
01:06:14,345 --> 01:06:16,097
Don't you read the papers,
knucklehead?

1061
01:06:16,306 --> 01:06:18,229
- Yeah, I read the fuckin' papers.
- I can't take this.

1062
01:06:19,434 --> 01:06:22,187
They got away. Grey Dodge.
Get after them.

1063
01:06:22,562 --> 01:06:23,859
How the fuck
did you know where we were?

1064
01:06:24,063 --> 01:06:26,111
- I can't take this.
- Shut up a minute. Did Eddie put you on this?

1065
01:06:26,316 --> 01:06:28,535
- Of course Eddie put me on this.
- That son of a bitch!

1066
01:06:28,735 --> 01:06:31,033
- You know I have a contract with him?
- You got a contract?

1067
01:06:31,237 --> 01:06:32,784
- Yeah, I signed it on Monday.
- He called me in Pittsburgh.

1068
01:06:32,989 --> 01:06:34,832
He said you were
fucking this thing up.

1069
01:06:35,033 --> 01:06:36,376
I'm not fuckin' anything up.

1070
01:06:36,576 --> 01:06:38,203
You should've been in LA two days ago.

1071
01:06:38,411 --> 01:06:41,335
Hey Marvin, don't tell me how to do my
goddamn job! I'm half-thinkin' not to turn him in

1072
01:06:41,539 --> 01:06:43,633
just to watch Eddie
go down the fuckin' toilet.

1073
01:06:43,833 --> 01:06:46,677
- See, that's a good thought.
- What? Who the hell's talkin' to you?

1074
01:06:46,878 --> 01:06:50,223
Yeah, who the fuck's talkin' to you? He's not yours
to take anymore, limpdick. He's mine.

1075
01:06:50,423 --> 01:06:52,551
[helicopter approaching]
Do you hear that?

1076
01:06:53,218 --> 01:06:55,346
Fuck! Now who the fuck is this?

1077
01:06:55,845 --> 01:06:57,847
[gunfire]

1078
01:06:59,474 --> 01:07:01,192
Jesus Christ!

1079
01:07:03,019 --> 01:07:04,362
Do something!

1080
01:07:07,232 --> 01:07:12,079
You guys are the dumbest
bounty hunters I've ever seen!

1081
01:07:14,197 --> 01:07:15,995
[gunfire]

1082
01:07:16,950 --> 01:07:19,453
You couldn't even
deliver a bottle of milk!

1083
01:07:21,955 --> 01:07:23,502
[gunfire]
[Jon screams]

1084
01:07:23,706 --> 01:07:26,129
Will you shut the fuck up?

1085
01:07:34,259 --> 01:07:35,932
Where the hell did he go?

1086
01:07:37,053 --> 01:07:39,727
- You think we lost him?
- I don't know. I don't see anything.

1087
01:07:39,931 --> 01:07:42,025
Oh, I'm sure we're completely safe.

1088
01:07:43,393 --> 01:07:45,771
[screams]
[gunfire]

1089
01:07:49,857 --> 01:07:51,655
[horn honks]

1090
01:07:51,859 --> 01:07:53,657
[tires screech]

1091
01:08:05,331 --> 01:08:08,255
- You all right?
- Yeah, I'm fine. I'm enjoying it.

1092
01:08:08,418 --> 01:08:11,297
- Marvin, Marvin, give me a gun.
- No fuckin' way!

1093
01:08:11,963 --> 01:08:13,761
[gunfire]

1094
01:08:16,175 --> 01:08:19,520
- Will you give me a fucking gun?
- Give him a gun, Marvin!

1095
01:08:19,721 --> 01:08:21,223
Don't fuck me, Jack!

1096
01:08:21,431 --> 01:08:22,557
Yeah, yeah.

1097
01:08:22,765 --> 01:08:24,563
[gunfire]

1098
01:08:31,190 --> 01:08:32,692
Shit.

1099
01:08:34,402 --> 01:08:38,032
They're not after me.
Just kidding, just kidding.

1100
01:08:38,239 --> 01:08:40,913
- Thought you threw those away.
- Always check the evidence, Marvin.

1101
01:08:41,117 --> 01:08:42,664
Those were car keys.

1102
01:08:46,205 --> 01:08:48,583
[screams]

1103
01:08:50,585 --> 01:08:52,258
[gunfire]

1104
01:08:52,462 --> 01:08:54,965
Son of a bitch! There goes $100,000.

1105
01:08:55,173 --> 01:08:57,847
$100,000? Eddie was gonna
pay you $100,000?

1106
01:08:58,009 --> 01:09:00,728
. Why? What was he gonna pay you?
<i>'</i> $25,000.

1107
01:09:01,679 --> 01:09:03,272
Son of a bitch!

1108
01:09:15,151 --> 01:09:17,370
[gunfire]

1109
01:09:33,002 --> 01:09:35,380
Holy shit, Jack! You got him!

1110
01:09:36,214 --> 01:09:38,012
[laughs]

1111
01:09:38,216 --> 01:09:40,014
Marvin!

1112
01:09:51,729 --> 01:09:53,402
What the hell are you doin', Jack?

1113
01:09:56,859 --> 01:09:58,327
See you in LA, Marvin.

1114
01:10:49,996 --> 01:10:53,170
[Jack]: Jon! Jon!

1115
01:10:53,916 --> 01:10:57,386
Jon! Where the fuck are you, Jon?

1116
01:10:59,547 --> 01:11:03,927
Give me your hand. I'm slippery.
I can't hold on. Give me your hand.

1117
01:11:08,389 --> 01:11:10,232
<i>Where are you gain'?</i>

1118
01:11:11,100 --> 01:11:12,522
Jon!

1119
01:11:14,937 --> 01:11:16,314
Jon!

1120
01:11:19,734 --> 01:11:20,986
Good.

1121
01:11:22,653 --> 01:11:23,950
- Promise you'll let me go?
- What?

1122
01:11:24,572 --> 01:11:26,950
Do you promise to let me go?

1123
01:11:28,910 --> 01:11:29,877
Fuck you!

1124
01:11:30,036 --> 01:11:32,084
- Promise to let me go!
- Fuck you.

1125
01:11:32,288 --> 01:11:35,918
You're making it very difficult for me
to do the right thing here.

1126
01:11:39,504 --> 01:11:42,303
All right. I promise I'll let you go.

1127
01:12:00,107 --> 01:12:01,575
Jesus.

1128
01:12:02,276 --> 01:12:03,823
- You all right?
- Yeah. Yeah.

1129
01:12:08,324 --> 01:12:09,951
Thanks for saving my life.

1130
01:12:10,743 --> 01:12:12,461
Thanks for lettin' me go.

1131
01:12:15,623 --> 01:12:19,719
I'll let you go, all right.
The second you're in LA County Jail.

1132
01:12:20,503 --> 01:12:21,925
Come on.

1133
01:12:27,009 --> 01:12:28,807
Yeah, that's right. Down here!

1134
01:12:29,428 --> 01:12:31,681
Are you gonna stand there
with your thumb up your ass

1135
01:12:31,889 --> 01:12:33,732
or are you gonna get me
the fuck out of here?

1136
01:12:41,315 --> 01:12:42,908
This just came in.

1137
01:12:44,861 --> 01:12:46,488
Is this gonna upset me?

1138
01:12:46,696 --> 01:12:49,449
I think it's safe to say that.

1139
01:12:50,825 --> 01:12:55,626
Are you familiar with a dish,
a potato dish, lyonnaise potato?

1140
01:12:55,788 --> 01:13:00,009
It's a kind of fried potato.

1141
01:13:00,209 --> 01:13:02,883
But it's got, like, an onion in it.
It's quite delicious.

1142
01:13:03,045 --> 01:13:08,518
It really goes beautifully
with steak, chops,

1143
01:13:08,718 --> 01:13:11,767
you know, hamburger, cheeseburger,
any of your meat dishes.

1144
01:13:11,971 --> 01:13:13,473
It's just a...

1145
01:13:14,056 --> 01:13:16,354
You know, I have... I have
enough money to buy

1146
01:13:16,559 --> 01:13:18,982
- Look.
- ...as much lyonnaise potatoes

1147
01:13:19,186 --> 01:13:22,816
- ...as you ever would enjoy.
- Just shut the fuck up, will you, please?

1148
01:13:22,982 --> 01:13:24,859
I just think you ought
to think about it a little bit,

1149
01:13:25,026 --> 01:13:27,074
because it's nothing...

1150
01:13:27,278 --> 01:13:29,952
Wait a minute, wait a minute,
wait a minute.

1151
01:13:30,197 --> 01:13:34,998
Oh, thank you, thank you.
Thank you. Very much.

1152
01:13:35,244 --> 01:13:36,917
Cover that.

1153
01:13:40,082 --> 01:13:42,926
Hi, you think you could give us
a ride to the next town?

1154
01:13:43,085 --> 01:13:44,837
- Sure. Jump in the back.
- Thanks a lot.

1155
01:13:45,004 --> 01:13:48,929
Great, great. See? For every shit,
there's six nice people.

1156
01:13:49,800 --> 01:13:52,053
- Jahé, everyone. Jahé.
- Jahé.

1157
01:13:52,261 --> 01:13:53,183
What's that?

1158
01:13:53,387 --> 01:13:56,391
It's "Hello." I can say "Hello"
in a lot of different languages.

1159
01:13:56,599 --> 01:13:58,897
Not yours, but a lot of them.

1160
01:14:04,482 --> 01:14:05,950
Welcome, sir.

1161
01:14:10,696 --> 01:14:13,825
- I'm not lookin' forward to this.
- What, do you think I am?

1162
01:14:13,991 --> 01:14:15,664
I don't understand the problem
with you two.

1163
01:14:15,868 --> 01:14:16,994
The guy's a fuckin' accountant.

1164
01:14:17,203 --> 01:14:18,420
Jimmy, it's been bad luck
right down the line.

1165
01:14:18,621 --> 01:14:19,873
Plus this guy Walsh is pretty good.

1166
01:14:20,039 --> 01:14:22,167
If he's that good, Tony,
maybe I should hire him to hit you.

1167
01:14:22,375 --> 01:14:24,753
I hope there's no chance of any
of this coming back to Jimmy.

1168
01:14:24,961 --> 01:14:27,180
No chance.
Rented the chopper out of Kansas City.

1169
01:14:27,421 --> 01:14:29,970
He's five times removed from you.
So you're clear of this. Don't worry.

1170
01:14:30,174 --> 01:14:33,144
Clear as shit, you fuckin' moron!
The guy is still out there, ain't he?

1171
01:14:33,344 --> 01:14:34,971
Let me tell you two guys somethin'.

1172
01:14:34,971 --> 01:14:37,815
I'm not interested in seein'
either of you two alive again

1173
01:14:37,974 --> 01:14:40,272
until you get the accountant,
you got the message?

1174
01:14:50,486 --> 01:14:52,864
[chickens squawking]

1175
01:14:56,909 --> 01:14:57,910
It's the end of the ride.

1176
01:14:58,077 --> 01:14:59,750
- This is it?
- This is it.

1177
01:14:59,954 --> 01:15:02,958
Is there a real... a real town
around here someplace?

1178
01:15:03,165 --> 01:15:04,917
- Channing.
- Channing?

1179
01:15:05,084 --> 01:15:06,051
Yeah.

1180
01:15:06,252 --> 01:15:07,469
How far is that from here?

1181
01:15:07,670 --> 01:15:11,470
- Thirty miles.
- Thirty miles. Jesus Christ.

1182
01:15:15,720 --> 01:15:18,269
[chickens clucking]

1183
01:15:19,348 --> 01:15:21,771
What the hell kind of town is this?

1184
01:15:33,195 --> 01:15:35,823
Is there someone that can give us
a ride to Channing?

1185
01:15:35,990 --> 01:15:38,163
Is there anyone going
in that direction?

1186
01:15:38,367 --> 01:15:39,584
No, don't have a ride.

1187
01:15:39,827 --> 01:15:40,669
Excuse me a minute.

1188
01:15:40,870 --> 01:15:42,918
Is there a bathroom
in there I could use?

1189
01:15:43,080 --> 01:15:44,297
Yeah, go ahead.

1190
01:15:45,332 --> 01:15:47,084
Is there a telephone here?

1191
01:15:48,169 --> 01:15:50,638
- Telephone.
- No, no, no telephone.

1192
01:15:50,838 --> 01:15:52,556
No telephone? Nothing.

1193
01:15:52,757 --> 01:15:55,055
[speaking other language]

1194
01:15:55,259 --> 01:15:57,853
[all laughing]

1195
01:16:01,849 --> 01:16:03,977
Glad you're all havin' a good time.

1196
01:16:05,352 --> 01:16:07,775
[engine sputtering]

1197
01:16:29,043 --> 01:16:31,421
Fear of flying, you son of a bitch?

1198
01:16:31,629 --> 01:16:34,473
Get over here!
Get back here, you son of a bitch!

1199
01:16:36,050 --> 01:16:38,178
Get over here! Stop!

1200
01:16:39,178 --> 01:16:40,521
Stop!

1201
01:16:46,102 --> 01:16:47,979
Fear of flying my ass,
you son of a bitch!

1202
01:16:48,187 --> 01:16:49,154
Get out of that plane!

1203
01:16:51,107 --> 01:16:53,360
You're a goddamn pilot,
you son of a bitch?

1204
01:16:53,567 --> 01:16:56,571
I didn't feel it was appropriate
to share that with you, Jack.

1205
01:16:56,779 --> 01:16:58,622
I'm gonna fucking appropriate
your head, goddamn it.

1206
01:16:58,823 --> 01:17:00,291
How do you turn this
fucking thing off?

1207
01:17:03,702 --> 01:17:06,751
Turn it off!
Turn it off!

1208
01:17:07,081 --> 01:17:09,834
Hang in there!
I'm gonna let it down easy!

1209
01:17:15,840 --> 01:17:17,638
Turn this fucking thing off!

1210
01:17:21,095 --> 01:17:22,938
Oh, shit!

1211
01:17:37,987 --> 01:17:39,955
Pilot? You're a goddamn pilot?

1212
01:17:40,114 --> 01:17:42,617
You're a pilot?
Here, I'll show you a pilot.

1213
01:17:42,908 --> 01:17:44,581
Let me tell you
about the coffee shop

1214
01:17:44,785 --> 01:17:46,458
I'm gonna open up
after I dump you off

1215
01:17:46,662 --> 01:17:48,756
and get my $100,000.
You're gonna love it.

1216
01:17:53,419 --> 01:17:55,296
All right, get back!
Get back! Get back!

1217
01:17:55,504 --> 01:17:56,801
Everybody back, back!

1218
01:17:57,381 --> 01:18:00,260
- Give me the keys to the truck.
- You can't steal their truck.

1219
01:18:00,467 --> 01:18:01,935
Shut up!
You were about to steal a plane!

1220
01:18:02,094 --> 01:18:04,847
- What are you talking about?
- I'm trying to save my life!

1221
01:18:05,014 --> 01:18:06,231
You're right,
I should give them something.

1222
01:18:06,432 --> 01:18:07,433
Give me your watch.

1223
01:18:07,641 --> 01:18:09,518
- My watch? Shit!
- Give me your watch!

1224
01:18:09,977 --> 01:18:12,400
Keep it. It's worth a lot of money.

1225
01:18:12,605 --> 01:18:13,447
Get in.

1226
01:18:13,939 --> 01:18:15,065
Stand back!

1227
01:18:15,274 --> 01:18:16,526
Get in.

1228
01:18:17,151 --> 01:18:18,323
Get in!

1229
01:18:21,238 --> 01:18:22,990
Jack, let's be fair about this.

1230
01:18:23,199 --> 01:18:24,792
You lied to me first.

1231
01:18:24,992 --> 01:18:27,916
- At the river.
- What? Get the fuck--

1232
01:18:28,120 --> 01:18:30,839
- At the river!
- You lied to me first.

1233
01:18:30,998 --> 01:18:34,377
- You got some fuckin' nerve!
- No. You lied to me first.

1234
01:18:34,627 --> 01:18:36,675
You lied to me first.

1235
01:18:38,505 --> 01:18:41,930
Yes, yes, I lied to you first
but you had no knowledge

1236
01:18:42,134 --> 01:18:44,102
I was lying about my fear of flying

1237
01:18:44,386 --> 01:18:46,388
at the river when you lied to me.

1238
01:18:46,555 --> 01:18:49,525
So as far as you knew,
you lied to me first.

1239
01:18:50,851 --> 01:18:53,320
Can't even argue with you.
I don't even know what the fuck you're talking about.

1240
01:18:53,520 --> 01:18:56,569
I'm just saying you lied to me first
as far as you knew.

1241
01:18:56,774 --> 01:18:57,525
Jesus.

1242
01:18:57,733 --> 01:18:59,485
- What's the matter?
- I got an ulcer.

1243
01:18:59,693 --> 01:19:01,115
- An ulcer?
- Yeah, I got an ulcer.

1244
01:19:01,320 --> 01:19:02,287
I got a big fucking ulcer,

1245
01:19:02,488 --> 01:19:04,536
and all your bullshit
started to make it bleed again.

1246
01:19:04,740 --> 01:19:05,957
You know why you have an ulcer?

1247
01:19:06,116 --> 01:19:07,834
Because you have
two forms of expression:

1248
01:19:07,993 --> 01:19:09,995
Silence and rage.

1249
01:19:14,833 --> 01:19:16,085
You should get some milk
to coat it.

1250
01:19:16,293 --> 01:19:17,761
Don't tell me what I need.

1251
01:19:17,962 --> 01:19:19,179
I need something to eat,
that's what I need.

1252
01:19:19,421 --> 01:19:21,594
What are we gonna buy it with? Dirt?

1253
01:19:22,049 --> 01:19:24,017
You drive to the next town.
I'll take care of it.

1254
01:19:24,218 --> 01:19:25,219
- You'll take care of it?
- I'll take care of it.

1255
01:19:25,469 --> 01:19:26,595
What do you mean,
you'll take care of it?

1256
01:19:26,804 --> 01:19:27,930
Drive to the next town.

1257
01:19:30,808 --> 01:19:32,526
But you lied to me first.

1258
01:19:42,653 --> 01:19:44,872
- Now what?
- Give me that FBI badge.

1259
01:19:46,532 --> 01:19:50,036
- The FBI badge?
- Yeah, give me the FBI badge.

1260
01:20:00,170 --> 01:20:01,171
Uncuff me.

1261
01:20:01,380 --> 01:20:02,927
- Uncuff you?
- Uncuff me.

1262
01:20:04,216 --> 01:20:06,514
Want to eat? Want a nice meal?

1263
01:20:06,802 --> 01:20:11,057
Want some of that shit you eat?
Come on. Uncuff me.

1264
01:20:18,439 --> 01:20:19,440
You fuck with me--

1265
01:20:19,648 --> 01:20:22,618
And you'll hit me on the head
and drop me in a thing.

1266
01:20:22,818 --> 01:20:24,445
Right. Come on.
Uncuff me.

1267
01:20:32,995 --> 01:20:34,963
- Who's in charge here?
- Who wants to know?

1268
01:20:35,164 --> 01:20:38,043
- Me.
- That'd be the manager.

1269
01:20:38,417 --> 01:20:40,419
I'd like to see the manager
as soon as possible.

1270
01:20:40,627 --> 01:20:42,095
Yes, sir.

1271
01:20:46,800 --> 01:20:48,598
Sorry.

1272
01:20:56,352 --> 01:20:59,071
- Yeah?
- Alonzo Mosely, FBI.

1273
01:21:00,647 --> 01:21:02,524
My partner and I have been
tracking a ring of counterfeiters

1274
01:21:02,733 --> 01:21:05,236
passing phony $20 bills
across the state.

1275
01:21:05,444 --> 01:21:08,243
Have you received any $20 bills
in the last couple of hours?

1276
01:21:08,447 --> 01:21:10,916
Yeah, sure,
we get 'em all the time.

1277
01:21:14,328 --> 01:21:18,208
You get them all the time. Would
you mind taking two steps backwards?

1278
01:21:20,417 --> 01:21:22,636
Would you mind opening the register?

1279
01:21:25,130 --> 01:21:26,803
No, don't touch them.

1280
01:21:28,050 --> 01:21:29,051
Excuse me.

1281
01:21:30,135 --> 01:21:32,308
Contract two, Hank. Check 'em out.

1282
01:21:33,680 --> 01:21:35,523
Give him a pencil, please.

1283
01:21:42,231 --> 01:21:44,108
Do the litmus configuration.

1284
01:21:46,026 --> 01:21:47,778
Doing the litmus configuration?

1285
01:21:47,986 --> 01:21:49,738
- Litmus configuration.
- Yes.

1286
01:21:55,577 --> 01:21:58,000
You seen any suspicious-looking
characters around here?

1287
01:21:58,205 --> 01:21:59,548
Nope.

1288
01:21:59,873 --> 01:22:02,672
- Do you live around here?
- Yep.

1289
01:22:07,381 --> 01:22:09,554
- How does it look?
- This one's bad.

1290
01:22:12,928 --> 01:22:14,930
Would you describe exactly
what the last man

1291
01:22:15,222 --> 01:22:17,645
who passed a $20 bill
to you looked like?

1292
01:22:17,850 --> 01:22:19,944
- Thirty. Tall.
- About 6 feet tall?

1293
01:22:20,227 --> 01:22:21,900
<i>_</i> 6! 5"-
- Dark brown hair?

1294
01:22:22,271 --> 01:22:23,523
Light colored.

1295
01:22:24,189 --> 01:22:26,032
- Sounds like our man.
- That's him.

1296
01:22:26,275 --> 01:22:28,152
We're gonna take
these bills for evidence.

1297
01:22:28,360 --> 01:22:29,236
Make them a receipt.

1298
01:22:29,445 --> 01:22:30,992
- This one's bad, too.
- This one's bad, too.

1299
01:22:31,196 --> 01:22:32,948
I'd like you to notify all
the other establishments

1300
01:22:33,115 --> 01:22:34,116
in the area of this situation.

1301
01:22:34,324 --> 01:22:35,701
What's the name of your establishment?

1302
01:22:35,909 --> 01:22:37,252
- Red's Corner Bar.
- Are you Red?

1303
01:22:37,453 --> 01:22:39,171
Yes, sir.

1304
01:22:39,371 --> 01:22:40,918
Do you dye your hair?

1305
01:22:41,081 --> 01:22:42,048
No.

1306
01:22:42,249 --> 01:22:43,626
Why do they call you "Red"?

1307
01:22:43,834 --> 01:22:46,553
It's short for Redwood.
My last name's Wood.

1308
01:22:47,045 --> 01:22:49,013
- What's your first name?
- Bill.

1309
01:22:52,050 --> 01:22:54,144
Thank you for your cooperation, Bill.

1310
01:22:54,428 --> 01:22:55,725
Hank.

1311
01:22:57,764 --> 01:23:00,142
These are all bad. Those are good.

1312
01:23:15,574 --> 01:23:17,793
- Come on. We're gonna get this train.
- What?

1313
01:23:17,993 --> 01:23:19,586
We're gonna catch this train.
Come on.

1314
01:23:19,828 --> 01:23:21,171
I can't catch a train.

1315
01:23:21,371 --> 01:23:23,169
You also couldn't fly.
Start running. Let's go.

1316
01:23:23,373 --> 01:23:26,047
Wait a minute. Wait!
It's a freight train!

1317
01:23:27,085 --> 01:23:30,931
I can't do this!
I can't do this!

1318
01:23:39,556 --> 01:23:41,650
I deeply feel I can't do this.

1319
01:23:41,850 --> 01:23:43,227
I thought you liked
to travel by train.

1320
01:23:43,435 --> 01:23:44,857
Get up there!

1321
01:23:51,235 --> 01:23:53,363
- What are you doing?
- Promise to let me go?

1322
01:23:53,570 --> 01:23:56,619
- Open the fuckin' door!
- See you in the next life, Jack.

1323
01:23:57,032 --> 01:23:58,830
Son of a bitch!

1324
01:23:59,034 --> 01:24:01,662
You son of a bitch!
Open that fuckin' door!

1325
01:24:15,842 --> 01:24:17,344
Glad to see me?

1326
01:24:18,011 --> 01:24:20,184
I guess we're in the next life, Jon.

1327
01:24:20,389 --> 01:24:22,687
- Don't overreact now.
- Don't overreact?

1328
01:24:22,891 --> 01:24:25,644
I won't overreact! Get over here!
Overreact?

1329
01:24:25,852 --> 01:24:28,651
You do this again,
I'll throw you off the fuckin' train!

1330
01:24:29,982 --> 01:24:31,404
Jack, Jack, it's a bad--

1331
01:24:31,608 --> 01:24:33,531
Get down there!
Put your hand in there!

1332
01:24:33,735 --> 01:24:35,362
- Easy, Jack. Easy, easy.
- There.

1333
01:24:35,988 --> 01:24:37,615
You son of a bitch!

1334
01:24:40,951 --> 01:24:42,624
- Jack?
- You shut up!

1335
01:24:42,828 --> 01:24:45,047
I'm not talking to you
for the whole rest of this trip!

1336
01:24:48,625 --> 01:24:51,925
Hey, you guys gonna let me go or what?
I'm telling you I don't know anything.

1337
01:24:52,087 --> 01:24:53,304
Is that a fact?

1338
01:24:54,298 --> 01:24:55,641
Oh, shit.

1339
01:25:03,557 --> 01:25:06,401
Why don't you quit?
It'd be cheaper for both of us.

1340
01:25:13,650 --> 01:25:14,822
Where are they?

1341
01:25:15,027 --> 01:25:16,199
You got me.

1342
01:25:17,237 --> 01:25:18,864
- Inspector.
- Shut up.

1343
01:25:19,031 --> 01:25:20,954
Now you listen, you son of a bitch.

1344
01:25:21,158 --> 01:25:22,876
I want answers
and I want them right now.

1345
01:25:23,035 --> 01:25:24,708
What do you want from me?
I don't know nothin'.

1346
01:25:29,541 --> 01:25:31,339
Sir...

1347
01:25:32,044 --> 01:25:35,969
It seems that an Agent Alonzo Mosely
and his partner

1348
01:25:36,214 --> 01:25:39,639
were seen hopping a westbound
freight train near Channing.

1349
01:25:42,262 --> 01:25:43,730
Come on.

1350
01:25:44,973 --> 01:25:47,396
[horn sounds]

1351
01:26:00,614 --> 01:26:02,207
- Jack?
- What?

1352
01:26:05,327 --> 01:26:06,954
How much further
do you think we have to go?

1353
01:26:07,162 --> 01:26:09,210
[imitating Jack]
None of your fuckin' business!

1354
01:26:09,414 --> 01:26:11,633
You know, because eventually
I'm gonna have to go to the bathroom.

1355
01:26:11,875 --> 01:26:13,172
[imitating Jack]
Shut the fuck up!

1356
01:26:19,675 --> 01:26:21,928
Did you ever have sex
with an animal, Jack?

1357
01:26:25,514 --> 01:26:28,484
Remember those chickens
around the Indian reservation?

1358
01:26:28,684 --> 01:26:30,607
<i>There were some good-Rankin'
chickens there, Jack.</i>

1359
01:26:30,811 --> 01:26:32,438
You know, between us.

1360
01:26:32,729 --> 01:26:35,778
Yeah, there were a couple there
I might have taken a shot at.

1361
01:26:39,820 --> 01:26:41,868
What's with you and that watch?
What is it with the watch?

1362
01:26:42,030 --> 01:26:43,907
You told me when you
get to know me better.

1363
01:26:44,074 --> 01:26:46,202
You told me about your feelings
for chickens.

1364
01:26:46,410 --> 01:26:49,584
How private could the watch be?
What's the big secret?

1365
01:26:54,126 --> 01:26:56,629
Gail bought me this watch.
She gave it to me.

1366
01:26:56,837 --> 01:26:58,931
It was the first thing
she ever gave me.

1367
01:27:02,759 --> 01:27:06,935
She, uh... she bought it
because I was always late

1368
01:27:07,139 --> 01:27:08,812
by at least a half an hour.

1369
01:27:08,974 --> 01:27:13,775
So she bought it and set it ahead
a half an hour so I'd never be late.

1370
01:27:22,779 --> 01:27:24,076
Somewhere in the back of my mind

1371
01:27:24,281 --> 01:27:25,954
I keep thinking we're gonna
wind up together again.

1372
01:27:26,116 --> 01:27:29,416
I don't know why I'm still hanging on.
I'm still waitin' around.

1373
01:27:34,416 --> 01:27:36,510
<i>1 don't think she's cumin' back.</i>

1374
01:27:39,087 --> 01:27:40,634
Yeah, I don't either.

1375
01:27:41,423 --> 01:27:42,891
I don't either.

1376
01:27:45,051 --> 01:27:47,304
Sometimes you just have to let go.

1377
01:27:50,432 --> 01:27:52,309
Just get yourself a new watch.

1378
01:27:59,691 --> 01:28:01,739
You're okay, Jack.

1379
01:28:04,237 --> 01:28:05,659
I think...

1380
01:28:06,448 --> 01:28:08,621
under different circumstances...

1381
01:28:10,118 --> 01:28:11,335
you and I...

1382
01:28:12,537 --> 01:28:14,790
probably still would've
hated each other.

1383
01:28:14,956 --> 01:28:16,799
[both laugh]

1384
01:28:19,711 --> 01:28:21,839
We probably could've been friends.

1385
01:28:24,007 --> 01:28:25,680
In the next life.

1386
01:28:26,802 --> 01:28:28,645
Yeah, the next life.

1387
01:28:34,351 --> 01:28:35,523
Yeah, great.

1388
01:28:35,977 --> 01:28:38,105
Accommodations were wonderful.

1389
01:28:39,731 --> 01:28:41,699
- You got a smoke?
- Don't smoke.

1390
01:28:42,859 --> 01:28:44,577
That fed took my cigarettes.

1391
01:28:44,778 --> 01:28:46,655
You want your cigarettes back?

1392
01:28:46,905 --> 01:28:48,953
Then you're gonna have to go
to Flagstaff to get 'em,

1393
01:28:49,115 --> 01:28:51,834
'cause that's where
your pal Mosely went.

1394
01:28:51,993 --> 01:28:53,836
[chuckles]

1395
01:28:54,830 --> 01:28:56,423
Just might do that.

1396
01:29:02,546 --> 01:29:04,219
Where do you figure we are?

1397
01:29:04,965 --> 01:29:07,935
My guess would be Arizona.
We've been goin' west all night.

1398
01:29:08,093 --> 01:29:09,811
I think we're almost home.

1399
01:29:12,639 --> 01:29:14,641
I'm almost dead.

1400
01:29:21,231 --> 01:29:22,403
Hey, look, John.

1401
01:29:22,607 --> 01:29:24,826
You know, the Witness
Protection Program isn't so bad.

1402
01:29:25,402 --> 01:29:27,575
They'll give you a new name.
You'll have a new life.

1403
01:29:27,779 --> 01:29:30,328
I'm not gonna make it
to any witness protection program.

1404
01:29:30,532 --> 01:29:32,751
- You don't know that, Jon.
- I know it. You know it.

1405
01:29:32,951 --> 01:29:36,455
Serrano's gonna get to me before I get
to any Witness Protection Program.

1406
01:29:37,038 --> 01:29:38,255
Do me a favor.

1407
01:29:38,498 --> 01:29:41,877
Don't pretend you care about me.
It really insults my intelligence.

1408
01:29:42,043 --> 01:29:43,215
I mean, let's face it.

1409
01:29:43,420 --> 01:29:45,639
The only important thing
about me to you

1410
01:29:45,839 --> 01:29:47,432
is gettin' your money.

1411
01:29:47,757 --> 01:29:50,636
You know, I'm really tired of you
makin' me out to be some kind of thug

1412
01:29:50,844 --> 01:29:53,063
whose only concern
is a big chunk of change.

1413
01:29:53,346 --> 01:29:55,895
Did you know that Serrano's people
offered me $1,000,000 for you?

1414
01:29:56,057 --> 01:29:58,810
Why didn't you go for the big money?
You're doing his work for him anyway.

1415
01:29:58,977 --> 01:30:00,229
I'm workin' for him anyway?

1416
01:30:00,437 --> 01:30:02,030
You don't know what
the fuck you're talkin' about.

1417
01:30:02,230 --> 01:30:04,574
The reason I do this shit
in the first place

1418
01:30:04,774 --> 01:30:07,072
is 'cause I wouldn't work
for that lowlife asshole.

1419
01:30:08,069 --> 01:30:10,572
- What does that mean?
- Nothin'.

1420
01:30:10,780 --> 01:30:12,373
Doesn't mean anything.

1421
01:30:16,745 --> 01:30:20,375
Serrano is the heroin dealer
you told me about in Chicago?

1422
01:30:23,335 --> 01:30:25,963
Who owned your buddies
and destroyed your life?

1423
01:30:26,171 --> 01:30:27,844
That's Serrano?

1424
01:30:29,841 --> 01:30:32,390
That's the guy
that you're takin' me in...

1425
01:30:33,053 --> 01:30:35,306
That's the guy that's gonna kill me?

1426
01:30:39,935 --> 01:30:42,484
Hope it's a wonderful
coffee shop, Jack.

1427
01:31:00,246 --> 01:31:03,125
- Come on. We're gettin' off.
- What? What? What?

1428
01:31:03,541 --> 01:31:05,669
We are getting off here,
Mr. Railroad Man.

1429
01:31:05,877 --> 01:31:07,254
- Come on.
- What? What? No, come on!

1430
01:31:07,462 --> 01:31:09,180
- You should be good at this.
- What are you talkin' about?

1431
01:31:09,381 --> 01:31:11,509
Come on!
Let's discuss this!

1432
01:31:22,560 --> 01:31:24,779
- Find anything?
- Not yet.

1433
01:31:25,105 --> 01:31:27,654
They could've jumped off the train
anywhere along the line.

1434
01:31:36,116 --> 01:31:38,084
Trains have regularly scheduled stops.

1435
01:31:38,284 --> 01:31:42,505
The reason for that is, y'know, because people plan
to get off the trains when they stop.

1436
01:31:42,706 --> 01:31:44,333
And that's how,
generally, people do it.

1437
01:31:44,541 --> 01:31:47,670
They don't, like, throw
each other off the trains.

1438
01:31:47,877 --> 01:31:51,051
That's the purpose of having stops.

1439
01:31:52,173 --> 01:31:53,220
What's this?

1440
01:31:53,466 --> 01:31:56,060
What are you gonna do?
What are you doin' now?

1441
01:31:57,595 --> 01:32:00,064
What are you doin'?
What are you doin'?

1442
01:32:04,185 --> 01:32:07,359
Oh, Christ, Christ!
Come on! Come on!

1443
01:32:07,564 --> 01:32:08,690
Are you kidding?

1444
01:32:08,898 --> 01:32:11,697
They're gonna come out
and shoot us, for Christ's sake.

1445
01:32:11,985 --> 01:32:13,237
What the hell?

1446
01:32:13,987 --> 01:32:15,580
What the hell?

1447
01:32:15,780 --> 01:32:17,908
Jesus.
Oh, great!

1448
01:32:21,619 --> 01:32:23,417
You get it started...

1449
01:32:24,956 --> 01:32:28,460
and I'll run you over.
That's the best plan I can think of.

1450
01:32:30,086 --> 01:32:31,633
[engine starts]

1451
01:32:31,838 --> 01:32:34,466
Congratulations. Another crime.

1452
01:32:34,883 --> 01:32:36,385
Come on.

1453
01:32:38,720 --> 01:32:39,846
I don't like this.

1454
01:32:40,013 --> 01:32:43,483
I don't like anything you do,
to tell you the truth. Nothin'.

1455
01:32:54,944 --> 01:32:56,241
Where are we going?

1456
01:32:56,446 --> 01:32:58,289
To the nearest airport.

1457
01:33:03,036 --> 01:33:05,539
[sirens]

1458
01:33:05,955 --> 01:33:09,084
I'm not the kind of guy that says,
"I told you so," but...

1459
01:33:12,253 --> 01:33:14,096
Oh, shit!

1460
01:33:16,174 --> 01:33:17,551
Looks like they've been spotted

1461
01:33:17,759 --> 01:33:19,727
around 35 miles south
of here near Sedona.

1462
01:33:19,928 --> 01:33:21,851
There are officers in pursuit.

1463
01:33:22,597 --> 01:33:24,144
Let's take the chopper.

1464
01:33:35,985 --> 01:33:39,535
This is- this is- this is the kind of situation
where something bad happens.

1465
01:33:43,368 --> 01:33:44,494
Easy!

1466
01:33:47,080 --> 01:33:49,208
Goddamn it, I don't like this!

1467
01:34:06,015 --> 01:34:08,063
[screams]

1468
01:34:08,268 --> 01:34:10,236
[horn honks]
Truck!

1469
01:34:49,601 --> 01:34:52,821
- Where are you goin', Jack?
- You'll find out when we get there.

1470
01:35:05,867 --> 01:35:07,335
I've come too far.

1471
01:35:07,994 --> 01:35:09,462
Too far.

1472
01:35:10,455 --> 01:35:12,298
I'm too close.

1473
01:35:39,234 --> 01:35:41,328
[screams]

1474
01:35:47,033 --> 01:35:48,626
[helicopter whirring]

1475
01:36:08,471 --> 01:36:10,974
Okay. I'm coming. All right.

1476
01:36:14,102 --> 01:36:15,604
- Come on.
- All right.

1477
01:36:25,989 --> 01:36:27,411
Here we go.

1478
01:36:27,991 --> 01:36:30,460
Hello! Hello!

1479
01:36:34,455 --> 01:36:36,583
Am I lucky, or am I just good?

1480
01:36:37,000 --> 01:36:38,217
Is that Marvin?

1481
01:36:38,418 --> 01:36:39,294
[chuckles]

1482
01:36:39,502 --> 01:36:41,095
Fuckin' A. I'm the best.

1483
01:36:41,296 --> 01:36:42,548
Marvin?

1484
01:36:42,755 --> 01:36:45,759
Hello, Jack, you dumb shit.

1485
01:36:54,142 --> 01:36:56,565
- Come on, you fuckin' pain in the ass!
- What was that?

1486
01:36:56,769 --> 01:36:57,941
Wait a minute.

1487
01:37:00,523 --> 01:37:03,117
If you move,
I'll tear your fuckin' lungs out!

1488
01:37:05,820 --> 01:37:07,288
See you in LA, Jack.

1489
01:37:32,889 --> 01:37:35,267
Shit.

1490
01:37:52,658 --> 01:37:54,456
Afternoon, sir.

1491
01:37:56,329 --> 01:37:59,128
- You're open?
- Oh, we're always open.

1492
01:38:02,085 --> 01:38:03,758
Hard day, huh?

1493
01:38:04,295 --> 01:38:05,638
Hard week.

1494
01:38:06,130 --> 01:38:07,882
Yeah, I know what you mean.

1495
01:38:09,050 --> 01:38:10,927
I could use a cup of coffee.

1496
01:38:11,803 --> 01:38:12,929
Yes sir.

1497
01:38:28,152 --> 01:38:29,825
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

1498
01:38:33,157 --> 01:38:34,329
Keep 'em.

1499
01:38:48,798 --> 01:38:52,348
Gee, I been lookin'
all over for these.

1500
01:38:53,052 --> 01:38:54,395
Thanks, Alonzo.

1501
01:39:00,101 --> 01:39:01,899
Marvin, I have to tell you,

1502
01:39:02,103 --> 01:39:04,982
I have this very serious
fear of flying.

1503
01:39:04,981 --> 01:39:06,153
Yeah?

1504
01:39:06,149 --> 01:39:08,823
Why don't you just relax
and sleep through it?

1505
01:39:12,613 --> 01:39:14,240
Forget your deadline, Walsh.
That's over.

1506
01:39:14,407 --> 01:39:15,579
That's the way that one went.

1507
01:39:15,825 --> 01:39:18,044
I know my rights.
You owe me phone calls.

1508
01:39:18,244 --> 01:39:20,963
What should be of paramount importance
to you right now is not the phone call

1509
01:39:21,164 --> 01:39:22,962
but the fact that you're
gonna spend 10 years

1510
01:39:23,166 --> 01:39:24,509
for impersonating a federal agent.

1511
01:39:24,709 --> 01:39:26,461
- 10 years for impersonating a fed, huh?
- 10 years.

1512
01:39:26,669 --> 01:39:29,092
10 years. How come no one's after you?

1513
01:39:39,056 --> 01:39:40,603
Give this guy his calls.

1514
01:39:40,808 --> 01:39:42,185
Thanks.

1515
01:39:43,603 --> 01:39:45,526
Can I have a little privacy, please?

1516
01:39:55,573 --> 01:39:57,871
[phone rings]

1517
01:39:58,159 --> 01:39:59,627
Moscone's Bail Bonds.

1518
01:39:59,869 --> 01:40:01,371
It's Jack Walsh. Put Eddie on.

1519
01:40:01,621 --> 01:40:02,622
It's Jack.

1520
01:40:04,499 --> 01:40:08,254
Yeah. This better be good news, fuckin' Jack,
because you got five hours left.

1521
01:40:08,503 --> 01:40:09,174
No, it's not, Eddie.

1522
01:40:09,378 --> 01:40:11,676
I'm callin' to let you know that
you're a dead motherfucker.

1523
01:40:11,881 --> 01:40:12,473
You understand me?

1524
01:40:12,673 --> 01:40:13,970
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

1525
01:40:14,175 --> 01:40:16,644
You put Marvin on this case,
you fucking piece of shit.

1526
01:40:16,844 --> 01:40:19,563
<i>You're fucking deceptive. You vermin!
You serpent!</i>

1527
01:40:19,764 --> 01:40:23,143
- Are you fuckin' done yet?
- You slime ball in a sea of pus!

1528
01:40:23,351 --> 01:40:25,524
- What?
- You blew it, all right?

1529
01:40:25,728 --> 01:40:28,652
You had the guy four fuckin' days,
Jack, four days!

1530
01:40:28,856 --> 01:40:30,984
You could've fuckin'...
you could've walked him backwards

1531
01:40:31,150 --> 01:40:33,403
and not fuckin' blown it,
but you blew it.

1532
01:40:33,611 --> 01:40:37,616
When have I ever let you down,
you fuckin' rat?

1533
01:40:37,865 --> 01:40:41,369
Are you fuckin' nuts,
tellin' Dorfler I offered you $100,000

1534
01:40:41,619 --> 01:40:43,792
when I told him I'd give him $25,000?

1535
01:40:44,747 --> 01:40:46,215
- When did you speak to him?
- What's the difference?

1536
01:40:46,415 --> 01:40:47,507
When did you speak to Marvin?

1537
01:40:47,708 --> 01:40:49,881
He called me fuckin', what, ten minutes ago

1538
01:40:50,044 --> 01:40:52,388
yellin' and screamin',
tellin' me to go fuck myself.

1539
01:40:52,588 --> 01:40:55,057
You're tellin' me, everybody's
tellin' me to go fuck myself?

1540
01:40:55,258 --> 01:40:58,011
<i>Am I supposed to just sit
on my fuckin' butt?</i>

1541
01:40:58,219 --> 01:40:59,971
Eddie,
what are you fucking'talkin' about?

1542
01:41:00,221 --> 01:41:03,851
Look, you got five hours left.
Can you bring the fuckin' Duke in, yes or no?

1543
01:41:04,016 --> 01:41:05,689
I thought he's bringin' him to you.

1544
01:41:05,893 --> 01:41:08,692
I just talked to fuckin' Dorfler.
He don't have the Duke.

1545
01:41:08,896 --> 01:41:10,819
- What?
- Where's the fuckin' Duke?

1546
01:41:12,108 --> 01:41:13,826
- Hello?
- I'll talk to you later.

1547
01:41:13,985 --> 01:41:15,828
Jack!

1548
01:41:49,729 --> 01:41:51,606
- Hello?
- Yeah, Tony Darvo there, please?

1549
01:41:51,814 --> 01:41:53,987
- Who's calling?
- Marvin Dorfler.

1550
01:41:58,112 --> 01:41:59,204
Yo.

1551
01:41:59,405 --> 01:42:01,328
<i>[Man]: I got Marvin Dorfler on the line.
Shall I put him through?</i>

1552
01:42:01,532 --> 01:42:03,125
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Put him through.

1553
01:42:03,784 --> 01:42:05,286
Marvin.

1554
01:42:05,494 --> 01:42:06,871
Everything still on schedule,
pal, isn't it?

1555
01:42:07,038 --> 01:42:09,040
So Dorfler's workin' for you guys.

1556
01:42:09,248 --> 01:42:11,216
- Who is this?
- This is Jack Walsh.

1557
01:42:11,417 --> 01:42:15,172
Jack, what are you complainin' for?
We came to you first, didn't we?

1558
01:42:15,421 --> 01:42:18,595
It's Jack Walsh.
Hold on. Somebody wants to say hello.

1559
01:42:20,217 --> 01:42:22,595
Hey.
Too late for you, scumbag.

1560
01:42:22,803 --> 01:42:24,055
No, no, no, too late for you.

1561
01:42:24,263 --> 01:42:25,810
I didn't come this far
not to collect my money.

1562
01:42:25,973 --> 01:42:28,772
You understand me, you motherfuckers?
I want the Duke back.

1563
01:42:28,976 --> 01:42:30,228
So what the fuck
are you tellin' me for?

1564
01:42:30,436 --> 01:42:33,189
What am I tellin' you for?
What am I tellin' you for?

1565
01:42:33,481 --> 01:42:35,279
I'll tell you what
I'm tellin' you for.

1566
01:42:35,524 --> 01:42:37,743
I got some of the Duke's belongings.
That's why.

1567
01:42:37,985 --> 01:42:40,659
Including some computer disks
that have every last detail

1568
01:42:40,905 --> 01:42:44,830
of Serrano's businesses
and his money-laundering operations. Everything.

1569
01:42:44,992 --> 01:42:47,711
<i>And if I don't get the Duke back
in the next two hours</i>

1570
01:42:47,912 --> 01:42:50,916
I'm gonna turn those disks over
to the feds. You hear me?

1571
01:42:51,123 --> 01:42:53,296
<i>You tell Serrano
I want to meet him with the Duke</i>

1572
01:42:53,501 --> 01:42:55,424
<i>alone in two hours in the main
terminal of McCarran Airport</i>

1573
01:42:55,628 --> 01:42:56,880
where we'll make the exchange.

1574
01:42:57,046 --> 01:42:58,548
I know he's the only one
of you fucking idiots

1575
01:42:58,756 --> 01:42:59,928
who won't try to take a shot at me
in a public place,

1576
01:43:00,132 --> 01:43:03,261
and if I see one fuckin' single goon
within a mile of that airport...

1577
01:43:03,636 --> 01:43:05,183
<i>Now listen to me very carefully...</i>

1578
01:43:05,388 --> 01:43:07,311
...the deal is off,
and I'm going to the feds.

1579
01:43:07,515 --> 01:43:09,609
I ain't gonna bother Jimmy
with your bullshit.

1580
01:43:09,809 --> 01:43:12,437
You're not? Okay, fine. Fine.
After he's busted

1581
01:43:12,645 --> 01:43:15,023
I'll make sure to let him know
you knew all about it beforehand.

1582
01:43:15,439 --> 01:43:18,739
<i>That's two hours from now.
Main terminal, McCarran Airport.</i>

1583
01:43:18,984 --> 01:43:21,328
You got that, moron? Have a nice day.

1584
01:43:28,119 --> 01:43:29,996
Tell Alonzo I want to make a deal.

1585
01:43:44,885 --> 01:43:46,307
You want to make a deal with me?

1586
01:43:46,512 --> 01:43:48,640
What would you do
if I could deliver you Serrano?

1587
01:43:50,975 --> 01:43:52,147
What do you mean, "deliver"?

1588
01:43:52,351 --> 01:43:55,025
For starters, conspiracy to destroy
government evidence.

1589
01:43:55,229 --> 01:43:56,606
What government evidence?

1590
01:43:56,772 --> 01:43:59,491
Will you let me take the Duke back
myself and collect my money?

1591
01:44:09,243 --> 01:44:10,165
Tell me more.

1592
01:44:10,369 --> 01:44:11,461
I'll have to tell you on the way

1593
01:44:11,662 --> 01:44:13,130
'cause we gotta be
in Las Vegas in two hours.

1594
01:44:30,765 --> 01:44:32,062
[JON] : Marvin?

1595
01:44:33,392 --> 01:44:36,066
- Marvin?
- No, it's room service.

1596
01:44:47,072 --> 01:44:48,540
Here. Hold this up...

1597
01:44:49,158 --> 01:44:51,206
so they know I took this today.

1598
01:44:52,244 --> 01:44:54,838
I amaze myself. I'm always thinking.

1599
01:44:56,415 --> 01:44:58,042
Got it all figured out.

1600
01:44:58,584 --> 01:45:01,508
- Now say, "Cheese."
- Don't do this, Marvin.

1601
01:45:04,381 --> 01:45:05,803
<i>Adios.</i>

1602
01:45:09,011 --> 01:45:11,013
All right.
There are no real computer disks.

1603
01:45:11,263 --> 01:45:12,890
- Is that right?
- Right.

1604
01:45:13,098 --> 01:45:14,645
So if you give him blank disks...

1605
01:45:14,850 --> 01:45:18,070
and he accepts them would that
still be considered an overt act?

1606
01:45:18,270 --> 01:45:19,943
If he just sets foot
inside the airport

1607
01:45:20,147 --> 01:45:23,151
he's committed an overt act,
conspiracy to obstruct justice.

1608
01:45:23,359 --> 01:45:25,657
When he shows up with the Duke,
you add kidnapping.

1609
01:45:25,903 --> 01:45:28,076
Anybody packing a gun,
conspiracy to commit murder.

1610
01:45:28,280 --> 01:45:29,702
The fact that it's an airport,

1611
01:45:29,907 --> 01:45:31,409
and Alonzo, correct me
if you think I'm wrong here.

1612
01:45:31,617 --> 01:45:32,709
I don't want to
step on your toes.

1613
01:45:32,910 --> 01:45:34,537
You can slap an interstate
transportation aid

1614
01:45:34,745 --> 01:45:36,497
or racketeering rap
on him right away as well.

1615
01:45:37,957 --> 01:45:39,584
Yeah, well none of that
bullshit means anything

1616
01:45:39,792 --> 01:45:41,715
unless you can get him
to take those disks from you.

1617
01:45:41,877 --> 01:45:44,596
Don't worry.
I'll get him to take the disks.

1618
01:45:44,797 --> 01:45:46,470
Get a wire on this man.

1619
01:45:56,767 --> 01:45:58,565
Marvin.

1620
01:46:00,604 --> 01:46:04,074
No hard feelings about
what happened back in Amarillo, huh?

1621
01:46:08,112 --> 01:46:11,491
Just one of those
spur-of-the-moment deals, you know?

1622
01:46:11,866 --> 01:46:14,335
- Where is he?
- Where's the money?

1623
01:46:14,827 --> 01:46:16,374
In the car. Where is he?

1624
01:46:19,665 --> 01:46:23,135
Slight change of plans.
Now I want $2 million.

1625
01:46:23,335 --> 01:46:24,006
What?

1626
01:46:24,211 --> 01:46:25,758
I read the newspapers, you know?

1627
01:46:25,963 --> 01:46:27,931
The guy got you
for $15 million, right?

1628
01:46:28,090 --> 01:46:30,684
So I figure he's gotta be worth
at least $2 million.

1629
01:46:31,969 --> 01:46:33,642
I'm a businessman.

1630
01:46:35,264 --> 01:46:37,141
How do we know you got him?

1631
01:46:44,899 --> 01:46:46,526
I want $1 million now...

1632
01:46:47,192 --> 01:46:49,069
and I'll call you in 20 minutes,

1633
01:46:49,278 --> 01:46:51,997
tell you where to drop off
the second million.

1634
01:46:52,197 --> 01:46:55,246
Once I know it's there,
then I'll tell you where he is.

1635
01:46:56,452 --> 01:46:58,204
Okay?

1636
01:46:59,038 --> 01:47:01,166
- Not okay.
- Why not?

1637
01:47:06,670 --> 01:47:08,513
What are you, fucking nuts?
What's Jimmy gonna say?

1638
01:47:08,672 --> 01:47:10,174
How the fuck we gonna get the Duke now?

1639
01:47:10,424 --> 01:47:11,676
You got the answer
right in your hand!

1640
01:47:11,884 --> 01:47:13,261
What are you talkin' about?

1641
01:47:14,178 --> 01:47:16,476
Joey, when are you gonna learn
how to pay attention?

1642
01:47:16,972 --> 01:47:19,395
Look. See what it says there?

1643
01:47:24,313 --> 01:47:25,439
All right. This is it.

1644
01:47:25,648 --> 01:47:28,151
Tonight is the fucking night.
You understand?

1645
01:47:28,359 --> 01:47:30,157
I'm sick of all of these screw-ups.

1646
01:47:30,319 --> 01:47:32,617
As soon as I get the disks from Walsh,

1647
01:47:32,905 --> 01:47:36,125
you guys drop Walsh
and you drop the Duke. Do you understand?

1648
01:47:36,325 --> 01:47:39,124
I get the disks, you drop them. Okay?

1649
01:47:39,745 --> 01:47:42,168
- I don't think you should do this.
- Oh, really?

1650
01:47:42,498 --> 01:47:44,091
What do you propose that I do?

1651
01:47:44,291 --> 01:47:46,714
Send somebody with a cash offer,
but don't do this.

1652
01:47:46,961 --> 01:47:49,055
I know Walsh.
He won't take any money from me.

1653
01:47:49,296 --> 01:47:50,923
He's a very self-righteous
type of guy.

1654
01:47:51,090 --> 01:47:52,307
It aggravates me.

1655
01:47:52,508 --> 01:47:53,680
In his mind, this is clean.

1656
01:47:53,884 --> 01:47:55,807
He gets what he wants,
I get what I want.

1657
01:47:55,970 --> 01:47:58,223
- The guy's a fuckin' burnout, Sidney.
- Hey, Jimmy...

1658
01:47:58,430 --> 01:48:02,526
Sidney, sit down, relax, have a sandwich,
drink a glass of milk. Do some fuckin' thing, will 'ya.

1659
01:48:20,619 --> 01:48:21,916
He's on his way.

1660
01:48:36,135 --> 01:48:38,012
<i>[Agent]: He's heading north
on Las Vegas Boulevard,</i>

1661
01:48:38,262 --> 01:48:41,266
<i>approximately two miles
from the airport. We're right on him.</i>

1662
01:48:41,473 --> 01:48:42,941
Why are you smiling?

1663
01:48:43,976 --> 01:48:45,819
I feel like a cop again.

1664
01:49:38,781 --> 01:49:41,500
So I'm finally in the
presence of greatness, huh?

1665
01:49:42,201 --> 01:49:43,373
The Duke.

1666
01:49:44,661 --> 01:49:46,709
The guy that steals money
from the scum of the earth

1667
01:49:46,914 --> 01:49:49,542
and gives it to the unfortunates
of the world.

1668
01:49:49,750 --> 01:49:51,798
I wanted to meet you face to face.

1669
01:49:57,925 --> 01:50:00,974
Did you actually think that
you were gonna steal my money

1670
01:50:01,178 --> 01:50:02,930
and get away with it?

1671
01:50:04,890 --> 01:50:07,359
I stopped by here
to tell you two things:

1672
01:50:08,227 --> 01:50:10,696
